## Implementation Steps

- [x] **Story 3.1: Define Core Content & Access Prisma Schemas**
  - [x] Update schema.prisma with Url model (including `id`, `originalUrl` (unique), `title` (required), `faviconUrl` (optional), `notes` (optional), `mobileSpecificUrl` (optional), timestamps, and relations)
  - [x] Add Group model definition (including `id`, `name` (NOT globally unique), `description` (optional), `displayOrder` (optional), timestamps, and relations)
  - [x] Create UrlInGroup relation model with `@@unique([urlId, groupId])` constraint and appropriate fields (`groupSpecificTitle`, `displayOrderInGroup`)
  - [x] Define UserGroupAccess relation model with `@@unique([userId, groupId])` constraint
  - [x] Update User model with necessary relations (`addedUrls`, `createdGroups`, `groupAccesses`)
  - [x] Implement proper referential actions (`onDelete: SetNull` for creator fields, `onDelete: Cascade` for join tables)
  - [x] Generate and apply migrations
  - Success criteria: Complete database schema for content entities with appropriate relations
  - Dependencies: Epic 1 (User Schema)

- [x] **Story 3.2: Implement Admin API Endpoints for CRUD Operations on URL Groups**
  - [x] Create API routes under /api/admin/urlGroups
  - [x] Implement group creation endpoint (with `name`, `description?`, `displayOrder?`, setting `createdByUserId` to authenticated admin)
  - [x] Add endpoints for listing, updating, and deleting groups
  - [x] Ensure proper sorting (displayOrder then name)
  - [x] Implement cascade deletion for related UrlInGroup and UserGroupAccess entries
  - [x] Add comprehensive error handling with appropriate HTTP status codes and clear JSON error messages
  - Success criteria: Complete, secure API for group management
  - Dependencies: Story 3.1

